Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
get_reinforce_pg_mode(25.10)                      get_reinforce_pg_mode(25.10)

Name
       get_reinforce_pg_mode - Returns the information for the specified para-
       meter

Syntax
        get_reinforce_pg_mode

       [-help]

       [-auto_ir_fix_effort]

       [-critical_path_slack]

       [-irdrop_hierarchical_block]

       [-irdrop_hierarchical_top_rail_analysis_directory]

       [-nonDefault]

       [-respect_defined_nets]

       [-respect_routes]

       [-respect_stdcell_geometry]

       [-timing_aware_effort]

       [-quiet]

       Returns  the information for the specified parameter. Note that you can
       specify one or more parameter. When you invoke this command without any
       argument, the software prints the current values stored in the database
       for all the options. If you provide an option, then the software prints
       the value currently stored in the database.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes the type  and  default
              information for each get_reinforce_pg_mode parameter.

              For  a  detailed  description of the command and all its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man get_reinforce_pg_mode

       -parameter_names
              Returns the information for the specified  parameters.  You  can
              specify one or more parameters.

              See  set_reinforce_pg_mode  for  descriptions  of  the get_rein-
              force_pg_mode parameters you can specify.

       -quiet Returns the current settings for the specified  parameters  only
              in  the Tcl list format. If you specify -quiet without any para-
              meters, the software returns the current settings of all set_re-
              inforce_pg_mode parameters in Tcl list format.

Related Information
              * reinforce_pg

              * set_reinforce_pg_mode

              * Power Planning and Routing chapter in the Innovus User Guide.

